Business Brief -- Coltec Holdings Inc.:
   Junk Bond Holders Clear
   Way for Recapitalization
Coltec Holdings last month began the tender offer for the
debenture issue as part of its recapitalization, which
includes a planned $577 million public stock offering and the
new Coltec Industries notes totaling $450 million. Coltec
offered to pay 107% of the aggregate value of the debentures
on the day prior to payment. About $881 million face amount
of the 14.75% issue is outstanding.
   The company, formerly Colt Industries Inc., was acquired
for $660 million in 1988 by Morgan Stanley  Co. and
affiliates.